# Plan sync is mandatory (no reminder needed)

Plans in `Plans/` are the source of truth for future humans and agents. **If you change reality, you update the plans in the same turn/PR — proactively. Never wait for the user to ask.**

## When you MUST update plans (same change as code)

| You changed… | Update |
|---|---|
| Folder layout, package names, monorepo structure | `00-MASTER-PLAN.md` §3 + current phase file |
| Stack, SDK, deploy host, tooling | `00-MASTER-PLAN.md` + affected module/phase plans |
| Schema / migration | `02-data-model.md` |
| API contract | `03-backend-api.md` |
| Store / admin UI routes or IA | `04-frontend-store-app.md` / `05-frontend-super-admin.md` |
| Shared package behavior | `06-shared-modules.md` (and package README if any) |
| Offline / sync rules | `07-offline-sync.md` |
| Billing math / GST / HUID | `08-billing-engine.md` |
| UI library / components | `17-ui-components.md` + `packages/ui/COMPONENTS.md` |
| Phase acceptance / deliverables status | phase file `10`–`14` |
| Non-trivial deviation from any plan | **also** append ADR in `Plans/DECISIONS.md` |

## How to edit a plan file

1. Bump `Last-updated: YYYY-MM-DD`
2. Add a one-liner under `## Changelog` (create section if missing)
3. Breaking-ish: add `> **Change note (YYYY-MM-DD):**` near the top
4. Prefer small surgical edits — do not rewrite whole sections
5. Never delete historical decisions — mark `Superseded by ADR-NNN`

## Tell the user (required — not optional)

Whenever you diverge from a written plan, your reply to the user **must** include a short **Plan deviations** section **before** or at the top of the summary:

```
### Plan deviations
| Plan said | We did | Why |
|---|---|---|
| <quote or cite plan file> | <what we implemented> | <why the plan was insufficient / wrong / inefficient> |
```

Rules for that section:
- Be specific (file + section if possible), not vague ("minor tweaks")
- One row per real deviation — skip if you followed the plan exactly (say "None — implemented as planned")
- If you need approval *before* diverging (new library, money math, destructive migration), **ask first** with options; only implement after confirm
- After implementing an approved or obvious deviation: update `Plans/` + ADR (if non-trivial) **and** still list it in **Plan deviations** so the user sees it without opening the MD files

## End-of-task checklist (always)

Before saying a task is done:

- [ ] Plans that govern this work still match the code
- [ ] Acceptance criteria / status checkboxes updated if progress changed
- [ ] ADR added if you chose something the plan did not already lock
- [ ] User was told **what** diverged and **why** (Plan deviations table, or "None")

## Hard nos

- ❌ Leaving plans stale because "we'll document later"
- ❌ Only updating code when layout/stack/process changed
- ❌ Waiting for the user to say "update the plans"
- ❌ Silently diverging from the plan without telling the user what and why
